P1.33 FIX SESSION - DNS Deletion

## Problem
Route 53 alias record deletion was using:
- Hardcoded placeholder: 'dualstack.placeholder.elb.amazonaws.com'
- Hardcoded zone ID: 'Z35SXDOTRQ7X7K' (us-east-1 only)

## Root Cause
ALB DNS name and hosted zone ID were retrieved during DNS record creation
but never persisted to infrastructure state. Deletion had no way to know
the actual values needed for Route 53 API call.

## Solution
1. Added state constants (types.go):
   - ResourceALBDNSName = 'alb_dns_name'
   - ResourceALBHostedZoneID = 'alb_hosted_zone_id'

2. Store during creation (aws.go:3783-3792):
   - Save ALB DNS name to infra.Resources
   - Save ALB hosted zone ID to infra.Resources

3. Use during deletion (aws.go:3811-3852):
   - Retrieve stored values instead of placeholder
   - Added condition: only delete if all 4 values present
   - Added warning for older deployments missing data

## Region Support
Now works in all AWS regions. Each region has different ALB hosted zone IDs:
- us-east-1: Z35SXDOTRQ7X7K
- us-west-2: Z1H1FL5HABSF5
- eu-west-1: Z32O12XQLNTSW2
(etc.)

